events.param: terminal LOG 124.12: Excuse my French, but screw these cowards. Patrick and I are leaving the other three behind, and we’re either finding a way out or we’re gonna die trying.

note I forgot to say, Edison died a few days ago. I’m the last original party member left. I guess that means everyone else was weaker than me. I wonder sometimes how you’d do down here. I think you might be weaker than you think you are.
party Huh, this dead end actually has nothing in it.

note These new guys are weird. I don’t like them. Their faces are wrong. Their eyes and noses are in the wrong places. They might be monsters but I don’t even know. This place reaches into our minds and twists up the information that’s already there. I don’t know what people are supposed to be like anymore.
note The craigslist listing said this place had all the answers. I don’t even remember what questions I was asking. That’s a dirty trick.
terminal LOG 100.7: Ancient ruins? You have got to be kidding me. What’s next, the mall? Am I going to go down a stairway and find a Spencer’s next to a Cinnabon? Who’s dumb idea was this place?
note *This page has a crude drawing of a monster.*
terminal LOG 123.19: We found another one of those strangely peaceful rooms and put it to a vote. It was decided 3 to 2, that we stay here forever.

note You know what, I may have lost my marbles, but the one thing this place has given me is a sense of humor. When we first started off on this adventure we were sooo serious. Now everything cracks me up. Blood is hilarious. Monsters are a riot. I’ve never had this much fun.
